1
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:07,960
DRAWING TECHNIQUE

2
00:00:08,039 --> 00:00:09,280
L.P.N.

3
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:29,160
You possessed kid. You ghost-seer.

4
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:32,080
- Boo!
- Possessed kid. Boo!

5
00:00:32,159 --> 00:00:34,400
- Boo! You ghost-seer.
- Possessed kid.

6
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,000
- Possessed kid, boo!
- You possessed kid, boo!

7
00:00:36,080 --> 00:00:37,400
Take this. Consecrated rice!

8
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:40,400
Go away, evil spirit. Yah!

9
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:42,440
- You possessed kid.
- Possessed kid.

10
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:43,720
Stop!

11
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:49,640
Ow!

12
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:08,600
POSTMODERN ARCHITECTURE

13
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:31,720
Wake up, Ms. Kluayhom.

14
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:35,800
Ugh. Why are you waking me up, Sompaen?

15
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:37,520
Huh? Still going back to sleep?

16
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:41,400
Get up, sis. Hurry. Wake up. You're late.

17
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,440
Five more minutes.

18
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,000
- No. Open your eyes.
- Ugh…

19
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:48,880
- Open your eyes.
- Five minutes. Really.

20
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,520
I just went to bed at 4 a.m.

21
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:55,720
You fall asleep while working
your whole life. And what is this?

22
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,400
- Ow…
- Hey.

23
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:03,120
Why would you redesign this?
If they told you to remove it, just do it.

24
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,680
It's so messy.
Not pretty at all. Remove it.

25
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,160
There's a crying sound.

26
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,600
Crying sound? Ah!

27
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:15,800
Oh, sorry, sorry. I was just joking.

28
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:18,920
Actually, it looks nice like this.
It's cute.

29
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:23,480
Hey, are you messing with me again?

30
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,760
- No.
- See? You always do this.

31
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:29,800
That's why things get messy.
I'm done talking. Go downstairs now.

32
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:33,760
Mom made toast.
If it gets cold, she'll complain.

33
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:35,880
Hurry.

34
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:39,080
- You nag like Mom.
- You're always teasing me.

35
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,520
Fine, I'm getting up.

36
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,800
Ugh.

37
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,160
Mm.

38
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:03,600
If I can't fight for it today,
we'll probably have to remove it.

39
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,560
I'm coming.

40
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,120
Oh?

41
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:25,520
<i>Enjoy your breakfast.</i>
<i>I'll go check on the kids.</i>

42
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:58,600
Hello, hello.

43
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:01,640
Mom, why does theirs
look better than mine?

44
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:05,920
Jealous of little kids, are you?

45
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,280
You're a grown-up now.

46
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:10,120
- I'll help, Mom.
- It's okay, dear.

47
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:15,640
Hey. Som told me you stayed up late again.

48
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:20,600
A little, Mom.
I had to revise a design for a client.

49
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:24,240
I don't want them to remove
the rose arbor. It's so beautiful.

50
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,520
- Hey.
- Hm?

51
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:28,480
Don't go telling people
about bad omens again, alright?

52
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:32,720
FRESH VEGETABLES

53
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,640
You won't make any money today.
Your stall will be ruined.

54
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,280
You foul-mouthed brat!

55
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,640
Are you cursing me? Get out!

56
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,760
You…

57
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:44,760
If you're going to run,
go that way. It'll be safer.

58
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,840
- Huh? Still taking?
- Uh…

59
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,320
Kluay.

60
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,280
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Let's go.

61
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:53,240
- Kluay, go.
- Teach your kid some manners.

62
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,680
Come on. Let's go.

63
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:59,360
You won't pay your debt
and you still dare open your stall?!

64
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:01,080
Well, what’s it gonna be?

65
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,920
Pretending to cry?

66
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,520
Too late to beg me now! Well?!

67
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,320
Mom.

68
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:15,040
Can I share some snacks
with Cartoon and Fifa?

69
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:16,920
Sure.

70
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:30,200
Why are you looking at me like that, Mom?

71
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:35,480
Okay, okay. I promise I'll zip my mouth
completely shut. I won't say a word.

72
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,840
So, Kluay what?

73
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:39,240
Kluay loves everyone.

74
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:42,640
But Kluay won't get involved in this.

75
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:43,800
Mm.

76
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:47,920
Very good. Go on. Hurry. Good luck, dear.

77
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,400
- Thank you. Can I have a hug?
- Yeah.

78
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:54,800
<i>Even though we're not related by blood,</i>
<i>Mama Toi has always loved me.</i>

79
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,640
- Please take care of this for me.
- Alright.

80
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:02,640
<i>- This is Ban Saeng Wan Mai, my home.</i>
- Hello, kids.

81
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:06,560
<i>Mama Toi took me in</i>
<i>when I was little and adopted me.</i>

82
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,680
You need a ride, Ms. Kluayhom?

83
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:16,360
<i>This is Som,</i>
<i>Mama Toi's biological daughter,</i>

84
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:19,240
<i>born not long after I was adopted.</i>

85
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,600
<i>Such a jealous kid, Sompaen.</i>

86
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:28,360
Ugh.

87
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,120
I'm in a hurry.

88
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,360
I'm coming now.

89
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,840
That dream again?

90
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,120
Ugh.

91
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,880
I only slept a bit.
Why does it feel so long?

92
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:17,640
Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat.

93
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,200
Here you are.

94
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,760
Is something wrong?

95
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:25,040
Do you know how worried I was?
I called and you didn't answer.

96
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:30,160
That was the fastest drive from Bangkok
to Hua Hin in my life. It was dangerous.

97
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:31,800
Mr. Arnon.

98
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,919
I had the same dream again.

99
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,840
You dreamed of that woman again?

100
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,240
It's happening a lot

101
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,640
ever since I came back to Thailand.

102
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:47,960
I don't know why. When I was in the US,

103
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,440
I never dreamed like this.

104
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:52,560
It's not strange to dream frequently.

105
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:55,600
You saw that woman
in the rose arbor house.

106
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,600
I'm planning to find time
to go take a look

107
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,680
after finishing my father's matters,

108
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,640
before heading back.

109
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:06,360
Mr. Warat, it's too late.

110
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,880
Mrs. Wanee ordered the demolition
of the rose arbor house today.

111
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,840
Huh?

112
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,720
Why didn't I know?

113
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,960
I didn't know either.

114
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:19,080
I had to find out myself.
She didn't let outsiders know at all.

115
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,960
Hey, but I'm not an outsider.

116
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,600
Where are you going?

117
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:26,560
Grandma has no right
to demolish that house.

118
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:38,480
This was the only way
to lure Warat back from Hua Hin,

119
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:42,360
because he loves his father's
rose arbor house so much.

120
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:47,960
With the utmost respect, ma'am. So,
we wouldn't need to order the demolition?

121
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:52,200
Once Mr. Warat returns to Bangkok,
you'll have me stop the work, correct?

122
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:53,560
No.

123
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,880
Because either way,

124
00:09:55,960 --> 00:10:00,400
I've already decided
to demolish that rose arbor house.

125
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:03,960
Back then, Wichan was ill.

126
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,920
But now…

127
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:20,560
Let Kluay continue her work,
just speed it up.

128
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:25,560
By the time Warat returns,
Kluay will have finished everything.

129
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:27,040
Yes, ma'am.

130
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,360
Thank you very much, Supol.

131
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:37,360
But the order I received was to remove
the rose arbor, not the whole house.

132
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:39,640
<i>The order just came today.</i>

133
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:43,200
Oh, but still, Mr. Supol,

134
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,800
I've already planted trees
all over the area.

135
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:50,880
If you want the house demolished, I'll
need time to move the trees out first.

136
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,920
I don't think it can be finished today.

137
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,480
<i>I don't know whether you can or can't.</i>

138
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:58,520
<i>My job is to receive orders</i>
<i>and inform you.</i>

139
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,040
Mr. Supol, just a moment…

140
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,880
Oh? Ugh.

141
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,520
Everyone.

142
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,200
Stop giving orders right now.

143
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:13,960
Get out. All of you, get out!

144
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:16,120
Get out.

145
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:19,360
All of you, get out. Go!

146
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,680
Who are you?

147
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:23,840
Who are you?
How dare you demolish my house?

148
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,080
Your house? That's ridiculous.

149
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,920
Or are you Mr. Supol's contractor?

150
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,880
- Can you give me some time?
- Get out.

151
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:34,120
Hey, why are you chasing my team away?

152
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:37,320
- Can you wait? Let me finish my work.
- Shut up.

153
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,320
Get out.

154
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,800
What is wrong with you?

155
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:42,040
You didn't listen,
so this is how it has to be. Go.

156
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,840
Help me…

157
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:35,320
- What's wrong with you?
- You…

158
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:38,480
Wow. So dramatic, huh?

159
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:39,880
You…

160
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,080
You need to make merit.

161
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,760
Are you crazy?

162
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,760
- Uh…
- Do you want to take meds? Go.

163
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:53,320
Help me…

164
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:56,480
Ugh, please let me go.

165
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,880
Are you okay?

166
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,640
- Uh…
- Should we take you to a doctor?

167
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:05,960
Please… please leave.
I promise I'll handle it.

168
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:18,840
Hey.

169
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:22,960
Hey.

170
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:30,960
Apply some pressure,
so the blood circulates.

171
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:34,400
Once she wakes up, go tell Mr. Warat.

172
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:39,080
Are you sure
we don't need to take her to a doctor?

173
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:43,840
Mm. She'll be able to get up in a bit.
It's just heat exhaustion.

174
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:46,760
Good. I'm too lazy to explain.

175
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:49,400
I didn't do anything to her.

176
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,680
I shouldn't have let you
drive back from Hua Hin alone.

177
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,400
Now look what happened.

178
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,960
That girl talked weird,

179
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,920
and she looked like she'd seen a ghost.

180
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,720
And she even told me to go make merit.

181
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:06,440
I think you two match well.

182
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,600
One has weird dreams.
The other talks weird.

183
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:10,960
You think that's funny?

184
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,240
Where's Kluay?

185
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,840
Are you the one
who had a problem with my sister?

186
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,400
With the utmost respect,

187
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:27,480
your sister is over there.
If you want to take her home, please do.

188
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,640
Seriously, both sisters.

189
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,760
Who did Grandma bring in to work?

190
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:43,680
Who? Because you refused to come help me.

191
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:46,080
So I had to get someone else
to do it instead.

192
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,560
Kluay is working for me.

193
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:51,600
I won't let you demolish
the rose arbor house.

194
00:14:58,760 --> 00:14:59,960
It's okay, dear.

195
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:04,520
Think of it as she trusts you,
that's why she came to ask for your help.

196
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:09,240
But I don't know
if I can stay and help her, Mom.

197
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:12,600
I've never felt this drained before.

198
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:17,440
Can't you tell her that you can't help?
That you can't handle it anymore?

199
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:19,320
I wonder about that myself.

200
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:22,400
I thought this new job
wouldn't have any problems.

201
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,040
But nope.

202
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:28,200
But I think what's scarier is Mr. Warat,
the chairwoman's grandson.

203
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:32,360
He looks so good, but his attitude…

204
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,080
Don't say that about him.

205
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:37,800
I went too far with him too.

206
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:41,800
And you need to watch your manners, Som.

207
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:44,640
Isn't he going to run Vanich Mall?

208
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:49,200
I'm in PR, Mom.
I don't deal directly with him.

209
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:51,400
But even if I have to see him,
don't worry.

210
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:56,040
At work, they call me
"Som the Die-hard PR."

211
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:57,720
This is nothing. Easy.

212
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,680
Come on, Kluay.

213
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:04,920
Let's go sleep. Get up.

214
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,400
- Kluay, relax.
- Ugh, you're heavy.

215
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:12,080
Alright, sweetheart?
Tomorrow I'll go consult Grandpa for you.

216
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:16,520
Right, Grandpa could meditate
and see who that woman is.

217
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,720
Hey, hey.

218
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:21,440
Grandpa doesn't have psychic sight.
He's just a devout man.

219
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:24,280
- Ah.
- Thank you, Mom.

220
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:28,320
But tomorrow, I think I'm going to resign.

221
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,000
- Again?
- Oh?

222
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:32,400
How long do you have to keep running away?

223
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,400
I don't know.

224
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,640
What?

225
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:51,480
Don't… Don't tell me.

226
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:03,240
- Mom…
- Mm.

227
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:09,040
Well, I won't…

228
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:11,599
I won't resign then.

229
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,359
Come here.

230
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:42,720
Oh my goodness.

231
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,520
Grandma.

232
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,400
Why are you so startled?

233
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,920
It's you.

234
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,560
If you wanted to come to pray.
Why didn't you sit next to me?

235
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:52,680
Standing there quietly scared me.

236
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,640
I'm not here to pray.

237
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,520
I'm here to talk to you

238
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:57,880
about Mom.

239
00:17:57,960 --> 00:18:00,520
If you have something to say,
why not talk outside?

240
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,120
Let's talk here, Grandma.

241
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:04,880
I believe you won't lie to me
in front of the Buddha.

242
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:07,960
Rat, can you speak nicely to me?

243
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:10,880
Grandma, I don't have much time left.

244
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:14,840
Do you even hear what you're saying?
Why are you cursing yourself like that?

245
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:17,000
Don't let me hear that again, Rat.

246
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:19,400
Grandma, you're the one being negative.

247
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:23,320
I mean I don't have much time left.
I have to go back to the States.

248
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:26,280
I want to ask you about Mom one last time.

249
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:29,840
Then I won't bother you again
for the rest of my life. Okay?

250
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:36,720
Warat, what's wrong, dear?

251
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,320
I had the same dream again.

252
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:41,480
It's okay, it's okay.
Come sleep with me then.

253
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:44,600
No. I want to know who that woman is.

254
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,920
You must have the answer.

255
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,720
I'll say the same thing.

256
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:51,800
I have never known
the woman in your dream.

257
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:53,760
So she's not my mother.

258
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:55,240
That's funny.

259
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:58,040
You can't even recognize
your own daughter-in-law?

260
00:18:58,120 --> 00:19:03,600
Enough, Rat. I don't understand
why you're doing this.

261
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:07,400
How many times
have you pressured me like this?

262
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:10,320
Then just tell me.
I just want to know who my mom is.

263
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,400
Stop shouting at me right now, Rat.

264
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:13,520
Huh.

265
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:16,920
When I was a kid, you told me

266
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,760
"You're too young.
You wouldn't understand."

267
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,000
And now what?

268
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,640
Am I old enough yet?

269
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,440
You're still cruel.

270
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:27,520
My dad is gone,

271
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:30,600
and you're still cruel
and won't say a word about my mom.

272
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:59,520
Arnon, I've decided.

273
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,880
I'm not going back to America yet.

274
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:03,960
I won't resign yet.

275
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:09,920
This isn't the first time
I've faced something like this, Mom.

276
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,240
Yesterday, I just lost it a little,

277
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:16,160
so I acted rashly and wanted to quit
and just be done with it.

278
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:19,120
But I think that isn't right, Mom.

279
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:22,200
It's good that you realized that, dear.

280
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:25,840
But you still have to
take care of your heart too.

281
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:28,560
If you can't handle it, don't force it.

282
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:33,200
I'll endure it. And I'll do this job
until the contract is fulfilled.

283
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:36,760
So, this job will be my last one.

284
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:38,720
What do you mean?

285
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:41,920
It'll be the last job I take
working for other people.

286
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,880
I've caused too much damage to others.

287
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:48,280
After this, I'll open my own plant store.

288
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:52,560
You've wanted to open one
for a long time, haven't you?

289
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,040
Yes.

290
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:56,520
Agreed. I'll give one more vote.

291
00:20:56,600 --> 00:21:00,920
This time, if there are any bad omens
that stop me from working again,

292
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:05,160
it'll be my own store. If there's damage,
it's on me, no trouble for anyone else.

293
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:07,720
But ideally, let there be no more trouble.

294
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:10,720
I feel bad for you, Kluay.
You didn't sleep again last night, right?

295
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:32,960
So you're not demolishing
this house anymore, right?

296
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,520
Correct.

297
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:41,400
If you're not demolishing it,
why are you throwing things away?

298
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,240
With the utmost respect,

299
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:45,320
these are all Madam's orders.

300
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,560
But the items are still in good condition.

301
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:52,760
Um, I think we should sell them
and donate the money to the poor.

302
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:55,600
I really can't respond on Madam's behalf.

303
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:58,920
But let me summarize the scope
of work you're responsible for.

304
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,040
You need to redo the entire landscape,

305
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:04,160
flowers, trees,
and also remove this rose arbor.

306
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:07,720
With the utmost respect,
these are all orders from Madam.

307
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,160
Remove the rose arbor too?

308
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:11,120
Yes.

309
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:13,360
Alright.

310
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:17,480
Such a shame. It's so beautiful.

311
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:21,480
Uh… wait.

312
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,320
Huh?

313
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:32,640
Hm?

314
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:41,600
Help me…

315
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:46,720
Uh…

316
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,160
Can I take a photo real quick?

317
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:54,920
Thank you.

318
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:10,320
Aw.

319
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:22,960
Investigate everything the way I told you,
then meet me at the office.

320
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:39,400
It's good that you're here.

321
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:41,720
I was just wanting to see you.

322
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:43,520
I came to see you too.

323
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:45,240
To see me?

324
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:49,560
Aren't you fully recovered?

325
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:53,840
Oh, no, I'm fine now.

326
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:59,200
But your grandmother has ordered we stop
the demolition of the rose arbor house.

327
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,360
That's how it should be.

328
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:05,760
That house will not be demolished

329
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,560
even if Grandma hadn't ordered it.

330
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:10,840
But there's something I want you
to go see. Please hurry.

331
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:12,920
Why should I listen to you?

332
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:20,280
Oh, okay. I used the wrong words.
Let me rephrase it.

333
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:23,320
May I invite you to go
to the rose arbor house?

334
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:24,600
Don't be sarcastic.

335
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,680
If you have something to say, say it here.

336
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:30,280
I'll only go to that house when I want to.

337
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:34,400
Yesterday, I saw a woman's spirit
standing beside you.

338
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,480
The same story again.

339
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:45,560
At first, I thought she was a vengeful
spirit, so I told you to make merit.

340
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,600
But…

341
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:51,520
- But…
- But what?

342
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:52,800
Today,

343
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:58,480
I saw that woman in a framed picture
at the rose arbor house.

344
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:04,080
She was wearing a white dress,
like a wedding gown,

345
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:06,400
standing next to a man.

346
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:10,320
I've seen that man's face
in the news before.

347
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:14,920
He's Mr. Wichan, your father.

348
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:21,440
I think you should hurry and go see it,

349
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:24,520
before it gets thrown out. Alright?

350
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:25,920
Don't tell me

351
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:30,600
you talked to my grandmother
about my dreams.

352
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,640
Dreams?

353
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:35,360
You know I dream
about the woman in that photo,

354
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:39,720
and now you're making up ghost stories,
vengeful spirit and all that, right?

355
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:45,760
You must've been hurt a lot
to never trust anyone.

356
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:50,800
Never mind.
At least I've done what I should do.

357
00:25:51,320 --> 00:25:53,600
And honestly,

358
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:56,640
I've never spoken to your grandmother
about anything other than work.

359
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:03,360
Oh.

360
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:09,240
If you won't go, that's up to you.
I've said my part.

361
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:25,400
This year's policy
hasn't changed much from last year.

362
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:30,240
Really? But other malls have been
scrambling to adapt to the economy.

363
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,400
Our mall is independent.

364
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:34,760
Chairwoman Wanee prefers it this way.

365
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:36,200
No stress, no care.

366
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:40,960
Profits are low, but if the character of
this historic mall remains, that's enough.

367
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:41,920
That's nice.

368
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:44,760
I'm a huge fan of Vanich Mall myself.

369
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:49,360
I love it. That fountain over there
looks just like what I saw as a kid.

370
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:53,600
Chairwoman Wanee got the idea from a mall
in London when she was studying there.

371
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:58,240
When she came back to take over the
family business, she did what she liked.

372
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:00,840
You really know your stuff, Ms. Som.

373
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:03,280
Just as I heard.

374
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:05,120
Die-hard PR, right?

375
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:10,000
I hope you'll have enough information
to update our website.

376
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:12,520
If you need anything else,
you can call me anytime.

377
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:13,600
Sure. With pleasure.

378
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,760
- Yes, let's continue over there.
- Sure.

379
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,040
Where are you going?

380
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,720
Oh, you're done with the restroom?

381
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:34,200
Not yet. The line's long.
I'll go to another floor.

382
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:36,240
Then go ahead. Upstairs, right?

383
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:38,400
I knew it.

384
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:41,080
No wonder you easily agreed
to come to the mall with me.

385
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:44,080
Turns out you wanted to see Som,
Kluay's little sister.

386
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:48,400
I had no idea she worked here too.

387
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:50,800
If you're not going to the restroom,
let's go home.

388
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:52,400
Why?

389
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:55,200
Have you still not moved on from her?

390
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,440
Be honest,

391
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:58,960
what's so good

392
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,360
about that murderer?

393
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:04,440
Kluay isn't a murderer.
She didn't kill anyone.

394
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:08,360
You know that very well.
So why do you keep calling her that?

395
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:10,560
It's been years already.

396
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:12,400
No matter how many years pass,
I'll still call her that

397
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,520
if you don't stop being interested in her.

398
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:19,800
Hello, Det.

399
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:25,480
Oh, Ameena, you came too?

400
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:28,080
Wow, you two.

401
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,280
You've been together for so long.

402
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:33,280
Hard to believe you lasted.

403
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:37,040
Move.

404
00:28:37,120 --> 00:28:38,720
What's the rush?

405
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:42,360
I ran all this way to see you.
Please update me on your life first.

406
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:44,920
May I ask,

407
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:47,480
has karma caught up with you yet

408
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:50,360
for spreading rumors
that my sister is a murderer?

409
00:28:51,120 --> 00:28:53,200
Uh, let's talk later, Som.

410
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,240
Please send my regards to Kluay.

411
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,320
Det.

412
00:28:57,480 --> 00:29:00,040
Keep your regards to yourself

413
00:29:00,120 --> 00:29:02,960
or give them all to Ameena.

414
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:07,320
Fake words belong with fake people.

415
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:12,640
They say
a rotten Jack may have as rotten a Jill.

416
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:15,120
I never thought
I'd see it with my own eyes.

417
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:16,960
You're the rotten one, Som.

418
00:29:17,040 --> 00:29:19,680
What?
Ameena, you low-minded so-called elite.

419
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,640
Oh.

420
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:23,800
How did we end up running into each other?

421
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:26,480
A secret reunion without inviting me?

422
00:29:27,080 --> 00:29:27,920
Sin.

423
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,080
Why are you here?

424
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:42,240
What are you doing here, you murderer?!

425
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:44,280
- Sin. Sin.
- Huh?!

426
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:45,800
Why are you here?!

427
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,880
What evidence do you have to accuse her?

428
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,960
My sister didn't kill your sister.

429
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:51,800
- Don't talk nonsense.
- She didn't kill her?

430
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,800
- Sin…
- You killed my sister!

431
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:55,000
Let me go!

432
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:59,560
<i>I'm the one who'll put your sister</i>
<i>in prison! You murderer!</i>

433
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:02,280
With a top engineer like you around,

434
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:06,160
my department's work
becomes a lot easier too.

435
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,720
It's not that big a deal.

436
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:36,040
<i>I think you should hurry and go see it,</i>

437
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:39,400
<i>before it gets thrown out. Alright?</i>

438
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:49,680
I saw you in my dream.

439
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:52,200
What's your name?

440
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:01,360
I should have believed you.

441
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,040
Startled much?

442
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:11,160
You sure you're okay?

443
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:15,280
Hey, why do you always
have to be so blunt with me?

444
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:17,600
Can't you talk nicely to me even once?

445
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:20,520
This house isn't being demolished now.
What did I ever do to you?

446
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:24,440
Look. It's already this late
and I still haven't gone home.

447
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:29,040
Uh, about that picture,
where did you hide it?

448
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:31,360
If you're trying to pick a fight,

449
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:34,360
I'm begging you, please stop.

450
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:37,320
I'm tired. I just want to go home.

451
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:38,800
Wait, wait.

452
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:44,200
Uh, where was the last place
you saw that picture?

453
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:46,440
When a worker carried it out
to throw it away.

454
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:48,080
Huh? Throw away?

455
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:50,000
Yes. I already warned you.

456
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:50,960
Who ordered it?

457
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:52,320
Who do you think?

458
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:55,280
This is too much.

459
00:32:03,040 --> 00:32:04,200
It's locked.

460
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:07,920
Don't tell me we're stuck in here.

461
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,920
- Hey.
- Huh?

462
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:11,080
Your phone.

463
00:32:11,840 --> 00:32:12,720
Call someone to help.

464
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:15,600
Uh… it's outside.

465
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:21,920
What kind of day is this for me?

466
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,560
Someone, help!

467
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,360
Traffic jam?

468
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:43,480
Traffic jams are nothing, Mom.

469
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:45,720
What I ran into was way worse.

470
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:49,560
I won't waste time guessing.

471
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:53,600
You can fight with
even an ant crossing your path.

472
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:55,040
If you want to talk, just talk.

473
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:58,800
- Mom, don't tease me. I'm already upset.
- Heh.

474
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:02,640
Mom, today,
I ran into Jirasin at the office.

475
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:07,320
Jirasin? Lakkana's brother?

476
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:12,640
I knew he worked at Vanich Mall,
but at the Chiang Mai branch.

477
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:16,120
I don't know why he suddenly transferred
to the same branch as me.

478
00:33:16,760 --> 00:33:18,560
What is this?

479
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:23,320
Both of my daughters
facing work problems at the same time?

480
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:27,200
I'm not afraid of him, Mom.
If he messes with me, that's one thing.

481
00:33:27,280 --> 00:33:32,400
But if he messes with Kluay again,
I won't let it slide like three years ago.

482
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:34,040
Hey.

483
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:36,360
Do you think he moved here on purpose

484
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:40,480
because he knows Kluay works
with Mrs. Wanee at the Vanich mansion?

485
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:42,480
That's possible.

486
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:46,480
All those times Kluay kept losing her job,
it was because of Jirasin.

487
00:33:46,560 --> 00:33:50,520
He kept spreading rumors.
That's why she couldn't stay anywhere.

488
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:55,400
Oh no. What if this time
he tries to destroy Kluay again?

489
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:58,840
No way, Mom.
He'll have to deal with me first.

490
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:01,680
Take it easy, will you?

491
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:04,720
You're tiny. What can you even do to him?

492
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:08,120
I think we should tell Kluay first.

493
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:11,480
But you two sisters' schedules
rarely match.

494
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:14,760
Or should I tell her for you?

495
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:17,360
No need. I'll talk to her myself.

496
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:20,159
But why hasn't Kluay
finished work and come home yet?

497
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:40,360
Hey, come sit down.
No one's coming even if you call.

498
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:44,560
Wait a bit longer, it'll be morning soon.
The crew should come by then.

499
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:47,400
Wait alone if you want. Are you crazy?

500
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:53,360
Has anyone close to you
ever told you how exhausting it is

501
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,560
to go against the world all the time?

502
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:02,760
It's so hot.

503
00:35:04,240 --> 00:35:05,200
So many mosquitoes too.

504
00:35:18,600 --> 00:35:19,600
Hey.

505
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:24,640
You know,
I couldn't sleep at all last night.

506
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:26,320
You want me

507
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:28,800
to ask why, right? Okay.

508
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:31,320
Why?

509
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:35,720
Ms. Mysterious,

510
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:38,880
the one I saw when I was with you,

511
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:40,920
she followed me to my house.

512
00:35:47,760 --> 00:35:50,000
You really expect me to believe

513
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,120
that you can see ghosts?

514
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:59,920
I think it'd be better if you called her
"her," you know.

515
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,200
Or if you apologize to her right now,
it's not too late.

516
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:14,200
If you don't believe me, why are you
looking around? She's not here.

517
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:18,600
Uh, that woman really went to your house?

518
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:21,560
Why would I lie to you?

519
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:23,560
But I get it.

520
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:28,640
No matter what I say, you won't
believe me. That's fine. I'm used to it.

521
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:31,160
How long have you been
seeing these things?

522
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:33,840
Since I can remember.

523
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:38,560
- <i>You ghost-seer! Possessed kid!</i>
- <i>Boo!</i>

524
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,880
- <i>Possessed kid! You ghost-seer!</i>
- <i>Boo!</i>

525
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:54,840
Why are you staring at me?

526
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:58,160
No, I'm not staring.

527
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,840
You're looking right at me.

528
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:05,480
I'm not.

529
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:08,240
I'm looking at something else.

530
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:25,520
So, you said you've been dreaming
about her since you were a kid. Really?

531
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,720
I dreamed of her before

532
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:31,000
I ever saw the photo of her
with my father.

533
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:36,760
At first, I thought she was my mother.

534
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:40,040
But then I thought maybe not.

535
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:48,440
Uh…

536
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:53,000
Do you want to know

537
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,680
whether she was or not?

538
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:57,880
Why would you ask that?

539
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:02,440
She's right next to you now.
Do you want me to ask her?

540
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:05,720
Seriously?

541
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:07,400
Yeah.

542
00:38:07,480 --> 00:38:09,400
- Be serious.
- I'm serious.

543
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:10,520
Left

544
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:12,120
or right?

545
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:31,120
Uh…

546
00:38:31,200 --> 00:38:33,240
You can't see her,

547
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:37,720
but I can see her clearly…

548
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:46,720
That woman has to be
connected to me somehow.

549
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:48,440
That's why we need her help.

550
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:51,200
<i>Ms. Mysterious really wants us to help.</i>

551
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:55,400
And I believe she's connected to you.

552
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:56,320
NEXT EPISODE

553
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:57,760
I need to find out who I am.

554
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:58,800
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
